This paper deals with the analysis of online communities and networks, which falls under the scope of social media analysis (cs.SI) and social network analysis (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for analyzing content on Twitter, which falls under the scope of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper deals with issues related to cybersecurity and online extremism, which could fall under the scope of cyber security (cs.CYBER) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
